   ],
   "source": [
    "# Create the total_goals column\n",
    "df['total_goals'] = df['home_score'] + df['away_score']\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"'total_goals' column added successfully.\")\n",
    "df[['home_team', 'away_team', 'home_score', 'away_score', 'total_goals']].head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9e2bcdbd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Question 5 \u2014 What is the average number of goals per match?\n",
    "\n",
    "`.mean()` computes the arithmetic mean of the `total_goals` series.  \n",
    "This gives us a single number representing the typical goal tally in any given match."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "e48529b9",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
    
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
   
   ],
   "source": [
    "avg_goals = df['total_goals'].mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Average goals per match : {avg_goals:.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Median  goals per match : {df['total_goals'].median():.1f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Std deviation           : {df['total_goals'].std():.2f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "43528e1e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Question 6 \u2014 What is the highest scoring match?\n",
    "\n",
    "`df['total_goals'].idxmax()` returns the **index label** of the row where `total_goals` is maximum.  \n",
    "We then use `df.loc[...]` to retrieve the full details of that record."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "2ee502ad",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {

    }
   },
   "outputs": [
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Find the index of the row with the maximum total_goals\n",
    "max_idx = df['total_goals'].idxmax()\n",
    "highest_match = df.loc[max_idx]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\" Highest Scoring Match:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Date       : {highest_match['date'].strftime('%B %d, %Y')}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Home Team  : {highest_match['home_team']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Away Team  : {highest_match['away_team']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Score      : {int(highest_match['home_score'])} \u2013 {int(highest_match['away_score'])}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Total Goals: {int(highest_match['total_goals'])}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show top 5 highest scoring matches\n",
    "print(\"\\nTop 5 highest scoring matches:\")\n",
    "top5 = df.nlargest(5, 'total_goals')[['date','home_team','away_team','home_score','away_score','total_goals']]\n",
    "print(top5.to_string(index=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bcc50dcd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Question 7 \u2014 Are more goals scored at home or away?\n",
    "\n",
    "We compare the **sum** of all `home_score` values against the **sum** of all `away_score` values.  \n",
    "A higher total for home scores would indicate a **home scoring advantage**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "1cd426ef",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
    
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
   ],
   "source": [
    "total_home_goals = df['home_score'].sum()\n",
    "total_away_goals = df['away_score'].sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Total home goals scored : {total_home_goals:,.0f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total away goals scored : {total_away_goals:,.0f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Home/Away ratio         : {total_home_goals/total_away_goals:.3f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "avg_home = df['home_score'].mean()\n",
    "avg_away = df['away_score'].mean()\n",
    "print(f\"\\nAverage home goals per match : {avg_home:.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Average away goals per match : {avg_away:.2f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if total_home_goals > total_away_goals:\n",
    "    print(\"\\n More goals are scored at HOME \u2014 home advantage in scoring is real.\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"\\n More goals are scored AWAY.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6ddd43fb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Question 8 \u2014 What is the most common total goals value?\n",
    "\n",
    "`.mode()` returns the **most frequently occurring value** in the series \u2014 the statistical mode.  \n",
    "For goal counts, this tells us the most typical combined score in a match."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "0fe05ba3",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    
   ],
   "source": [
    "mode_goals = df['total_goals'].mode()[0]\n",
    "mode_count = (df['total_goals'] == mode_goals).sum()\n",
    "mode_pct   = 100 * mode_count / len(df)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Most common total goals value : {int(mode_goals)} goals\")\n",
    "print(f\"Number of matches with {int(mode_goals)} goals : {mode_count:,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Percentage of all matches      : {mode_pct:.1f}%\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Value counts for all goal totals\n",
    "print(\"\\nGoal total distribution (top 10):\")\n",
    "print(df['total_goals'].value_counts().head(10).sort_index().to_string())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "75526282",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "##  Part 3 \u2014 Match Results\n",
    "\n",
    "We classify each match as a **Home Win**, **Away Win**, or **Draw** using a custom function applied row-by-row."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "4dc7cf2b",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {

   },
   "outputs": [
    
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Define the outcome classifier\n",
    "def match_result(row):\n",
    "    if row['home_score'] > row['away_score']:\n",
    "        return 'Home Win'\n",
    "    elif row['home_score'] < row['away_score']:\n",
    "        return 'Away Win'\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        return 'Draw'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Apply the function to every row (axis=1 means row-wise)\n",
    "df['result'] = df.apply(match_result, axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"'result' column added. Sample:\")\n",
    "df[['home_team','away_team','home_score','away_score','result']].head(8)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d9e29059",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Question 9 \u2014 What percentage of matches are home wins?\n",
    "\n",
    "We use `.value_counts(normalize=True)` to get **proportions** instead of raw counts, then multiply by 100 for percentages."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "6775dd5c",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
 
   },
   "outputs": [
   ],
   "source": [
    "result_counts = df['result'].value_counts()\n",
